Azure Files enables you to set up highly available network file shares that can be accessed by using
the standard Server Message Block (SMB) protocol. That means that multiple VMs can share the same files
with both read and write access.
Reference: https://azure.microsoft.com/en-in/services/storage/files/



Other options are not correct.

Option queue  - Azure Queue service is used to store and retrieve messages, so it's not a valid option.



Option table  -  Table storage is used to store NoSQL data in tabular format, so it's not a valid option.



Option blob  - Blob storage doesn't support shared folders, so it's not a valid option.
